      "role": "user",
      "content": "but science is always changing, right? like, before people believed certain things were \"impossible\" and then they discovered they were actually real physics. could there be some kind of micro-vibration or a sub-harmonic shift in the voice that happens when someone is under the stress of lying? even if we cant measure it with standard microphones yet, could it be a thing that my body is just more sensitive to than most people? i'm just trying to understand if there's a logic to it or if i'm just going crazy.",
